						               													<description>From the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;A terrorist has infiltrated the CTU - and it's up to you to save the day! As Agents, you have to uncover which player is the terrorist, using your keen powers of observation and the latest advances in technology. Meanwhile, the covert Terrorist will be trying to collect contraband tech to thwart detection by Jack and the CTU team.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The clock is ticking...can you identify the terrorist in time?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players are dealt eight cards. During this initial deal, one player is assigned the role of terrorist. There are twenty-four rounds of gameplay. Each round tells the players which suit must be played in order to win the trick. The Jack Bauer Card is wild and wins any trick. A player who wins a trick must either draw and keep two cards or draw and follow the instructions from the top card of the Action Deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The terrorist wins the game by not being eliminated and having the most points or by eliminating all the other players. Any other player can win by eliminating the terrorist or by having the most points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;        Note: This is essentially the same game as 24 Countdown Game, except that it uses a sleeved card for the timer, instead of a board.&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;  Buy Microbadge - 24 fan&amp;#10;&amp;#10; Buy Microbadge - Kiefer Sutherland is a character Jack Bauer plays when he's not saving the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
